Model 1: A convolutional neural network (CNN) based on the Inception V3 model, used to analyze arthroscopic images.
Model 2: A MultiLayer Perceptron (MLP) model, built to process medical data (clinical and paraclinical data).
Model 3: A combination of the CNN from Model 1 and the MLP from Model 2, integrating both image and medical data
